Usage: place_partition_clone [-help] -hinst <partition_clone_hinst_name>
                             -location {x y} [-orient {R0 R180 MX MY}]
                             [-skip_sync] [-sync_objs <string>]

-help                                   # Prints out the command usage
-hinst <partition_clone_hinst_name>     # Specifies the name of partition clone
                                        # hierarchical instance (string, required)
-location {x y}                         # Specifies location of the clone
                                        # partition (point, required)
-orient {R0 R180 MX MY}                 # Specifies orientation of the clone
                                        # partition (enum, optional)
-skip_sync                              # Skips sync from ref hinst to target
                                        # hinsts (bool, optional)
-sync_objs <string>                     # Specifies objects to be synced from
                                        # reference hinst. {placeBlockage
                                        # routeBlockage pinBlockage macros
                                        # fences} (string, optional)